(3 inline comments)

Do we need also pass location's metadata into store interface?probably store need it (or hits for better handling?).

Patch Set 8: (3 inline comments)

Passing the information back into the store may be a good future enhancement.  However it is not the intention of this patch.  This patch is allowing the storage system to present addition information to the user to consume, and not a way to tie information to a location for its own consumption.  What you mention may very well be useful in a future patch but I would greatly prefer to not further complicate this patch with an interface change like that.

Majority of notes are minor fixups.

But looking at the schema I think we should talk about how permissive this patch is with what kinds of metadata stores can return, and how we represent that metadata in the apis.

Hi John,

Just regarding the v1 locations leaking I mentioned in PS 9 - here's what reproduced it for me, will re-visit the rest of the changes soon.

* <Spin up a fresh devstack instance>
* git review -d 34492 # PS 14
* <Stop glance-registry>
* glance-manage db_sync
* <Start glance-registry>
* <Restart glance-api>
* export TOKEN=$(keystone token-get | grep ' id ' | get_field 2)
* curl -H"x-auth-token:$TOKEN" http://localhost:9292/v1/images/7144a5e6-cbb5-4ebc-8cee-3587adc38468 -v

< X-Image-Meta-Location_data: [{u'url': u'swift+http://service%3Aglance:glance@1.2.3.4:5000/v2.0/glance/7144a5e6-cbb5-4ebc-8cee-3587adc38468', u'metadata': {}}]

Note, I had to run the curl twice, it didn't seem to happen on the first try, but happens consistently thereafter.
